main event: A civilian reported a sighting of a bright object in the sky over Kansas City, Missouri on March 1, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes., The object was observed moving south at 25 degrees elevation., The conclusion suggested it was a known satellite in the vicinity., Witnesses described the object as much larger and brighter than a star., Multiple reports indicated sightings of objects moving southeast around the same time.
sighted object: One bright object resembling a very large star
witness description: A couple involved in delivering literature for a dairy council, noted for their sincerity and reliability
